"The city of Constantinople was long abandoned, its streets silent and still. The sun beat down, casting long shadows that seemed to writhe across the cobblestones like living things. I had seen nothing but decay and ruin since I entered this forsaken place. My back ached from the weight of my armor, but I pressed on, driven by a morbid curiosity.

