I found Kailyn in the study, her eyes sunken, her skin gray as the stone walls. She didn't seem to notice me at first, her gaze fixed on something in her hands. As I drew closer, I saw it was her own lung, a grotesque, pulsing orb that seemed to breathe of its own accord.

